adjectives.description: maidish (comparative more maidish, superlative most maidish)

entries.meaning: Resembling or characteristic of a maid; effeminate.

examples: In December 1919 she was forty-five years old and more aware than ever that her destiny was to be a maidish one: to look after her ageing mother (by whom she was permanently irritated), to offer emotional succour to her younger siblings  […]
